# Design Color Standard

Use a single color system for all future screen outputs. Do not introduce random new hues.

## Core Palette (Allowed)
- Primary: `#2563EB`
- Primary Text/Dark: `#1E3A8A`, `#1F2937`, `#111827`
- Secondary Text: `#334155`, `#64748B`, `#94A3B8`, `#9CA3AF`
- Background: `#F5F7FB`, `#FFFFFF`, `#F8FAFC`, `#EEF2F7`
- Border/Divider: `#E2E8F0`, `#CBD5E1`, `#D1D5DB`, `#E5E7EB`
- Warning/Attention: `#F59E0B`, `#FB923C`, `#B45309`, `#C2410C`
- Soft Warning BG: `#FEF3C7`, `#FFEDD5`
- Accent (small badge only): `#D5B8FD`

## Usage Rules
- Keep page-level colors in neutral + primary only.
- Warning colors are only for risk tags, warning chips, and key attention hints.
- Accent purple is only for small badges; never use as large surface background.
- Card/background/border must come from the allowed neutral set.
- If unsure, prefer existing page colors rather than adding a new one.

## Interactive State Rules (Mandatory)
- For tab/nav/filter state switching, exactly one item can be active at a time.
- When switching active item, remove ALL active residues from previous item:
  - active fill/background
  - active text/icon color
  - active border/stroke
  - active shadow/effect
- Inactive items must use a single unified inactive style (same fill, text/icon color, border behavior).
- Never leave mixed states like: inactive text with active border, or inactive fill with active shadow.

## State-Switch QA Checklist (Run every time)
- [ ] Active item is visually unique and complete (fill + text/icon).
- [ ] All non-active siblings are style-consistent with each other.
- [ ] No residual border/shadow/highlight remains on previous active item.
- [ ] Screenshot check completed for the whole nav/filter group, not only the edited node.
